This layout automatically adapts to the available screen width without requiring media queries.

Industry Best Practices
Start with a mobile-first approach.
Use Flexbox for one-dimensional layouts (rows or columns).
Use CSS Grid for two-dimensional layouts.
Prefer relative units like %, rem, vw, and vh over fixed px where appropriate.
Make images responsive using max-width: 100%.
Use auto-fit/auto-fill with minmax() for flexible grid layouts.
Use media queries only when the design truly needs them.
Test on real devices and in browser developer tools.

Once you're comfortable with these concepts, you can build responsive landing pages, dashboards, e-commerce sites, and React applications that work well across a wide range of screen sizes.

