## This combines several modern units:
% for responsive container width
rem for consistent spacing and typography
vh for a full-screen hero section
ch for readable line lengths
fr for flexible grid columns
clamp() for responsive text sizing

 Use Case                 Recommended Unit          
 Font size            | rem                     
 Margins & Padding    | rem                     
 Container width      | % + max-width         
 Images               | % + max-width: 100%  
 Full-screen sections | vh                      
 Responsive text      | clamp() with rem/vw 
 CSS Grid columns     | fr                      
 Input width          | ch                      
 Borders              | px                      

## Rule of Thumb
- Use rem for typography and spacing
- Use % for flexible layouts
- Use vw and vh when sizing relative to the viewport
- Use fr in CSS Grid
- Use px sparingly for elements that truly need fixed dimensions, such as thin borders or small icons
